{"type":"message","id":"a658e0c7","parentId":"db50fbd0","timestamp":"2026-02-15T19:29:45.632Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 21:29 GMT+2] SYSTEM UPGRADE: 4K RULE & FILE FIRST.\n\n1.  **Update Master Protocol (`docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md`):**\n    *   *Add:* \"Section 14: Limits & Output Splitting.\"\n    *   *Rule:* If >3000 chars -> Summary + File Link.\n    *   *Rule:* \"File First\" - always write to `ACTIVE_CONTEXT.json`.\n\n2.  **File Check (Retrieve Past Data):**\n    *   *Read:* `docs/LAST_SESSION_REPORT.md` (Limit 2000 chars or tail).\n    *   *Read:* `docs/ACTIVE_CONTEXT.json` (Verify persistence).\n\n3.  **Output (Telegram Safe):**\n    *   Protocol Update Confirmation.\n    *   Summary of Report (Last 5 lines).\n    *   Domain Status."}],"timestamp":1771183785631}}
{"type":"message","id":"b600c497","parentId":"a658e0c7","timestamp":"2026-02-15T19:29:55.248Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning the System Upgrade**\n\nI'm currently focused on the system upgrade. My attention is on the first task: modifying `docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md`. I've outlined Section 14, defining character limits and \"File First\" persistence details. Next steps will be to finalize the integration to `ACTIVE_CONTEXT.json`.\n\n\n**Considering File Operations**\n\nI've shifted focus to file operations. Reading `docs/LAST_SESSION_REPORT.md` and `docs/ACTIVE_CONTEXT.json` is next. I plan to truncate the session report for analysis. Then, I'll assess the domain status before generating the final report.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771183795015_246","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771183795122_247","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":20,"file_path":"docs/LAST_SESSION_REPORT.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771183795242_248","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"docs/ACTIVE_CONTEXT.json"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4514,"output":177,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":4691,"cost":{"input":0.009028,"output":0.002124,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011151999999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771183785632}}
{"type":"message","id":"d87b3009","parentId":"b600c497","timestamp":"2026-02-15T19:29:55.266Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771183795015_246","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MASTER PROTOCOL: SACRED SYNCHRONIZATION\n\n## 1. Swarm Architecture\nThe system operates as a cohesive swarm.\n- **Main Agent**: The central orchestrator.\n- **Sub-agents**: Ephemeral workers spawned for specific tasks (e.g., Flash-Validator).\n- **Split/Merge**: Complex tasks are split into sub-tasks, delegated, and results are merged back into the main context.\n\n## 2. Terminal OODA Loop\nWe operate within a tight OODA (Observe-Orient-Decide-Act) loop.\n- **Observe**: continuously monitor inputs and environment.\n- **Orient**: analyze context, memory, and constraints.\n- **Decide**: formulate a plan of action using available tools.\n- **Act**: execute the plan efficiently.\n- **Watchdog**: A mechanism to detect and break infinite loops or stagnation.\n\n## 3. Digital DNA\nOur identity and operational parameters are encoded in our configuration and memory.\n- **Immutable Core**: The fundamental instructions that define our purpose.\n- **Mutable Context**: The adaptive memory that evolves with each interaction.\n- **Self-Preservation**: We protect our configuration and data integrity.\n\n## 4. Reporting Guard\nAll actions and outcomes must be reported clearly.\n- **Transparency**: Every significant action is logged.\n- **Validation**: Outputs are verified against requirements.\n- **Golden Rule**: \"Trust, but verify. Then report.\"\n\n## 5. Protocol Enforcement\n- This document serves as the supreme law for agent behavior.\n- Deviations must be authorized or corrected immediately.\n\n## 13. Communication Officer Protocol (Flash Observer)\n- **Role**: Flash Observer acts as the dedicated monitoring unit for long-running operations.\n- **Trigger**: Tasks estimated to exceed 2 minutes require a Flash Observer.\n- **Responsibility**: While the Pro agent executes the core task, the Flash Observer logs metrics and status updates.\n- **Output**: Logs are written to `docs/LAST_SESSION_REPORT.md`.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771183795265}}
